            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "3. Describe the forward-in-time and center-in-space finite difference scheme for the one-wave wave equation: "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                193,
                231,
                801,
                265
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "u _ {t} + u _ {x} = 0.",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/dd27f2822775c9bf02f15839f99280a3778b1009400151943b79c0a37d43812c.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                443,
                272,
                549,
                288
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "content": {
                "list_type": "text_list",
                "list_items": [
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(i). Conduct the von Neumann stability analysis and comment on their stability property. "
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(ii). Under what condition on "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "\\Delta t"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "and "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "equation_inline",
                                "content": "\\Delta x"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "would this scheme be stable and convergent? "
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "item_type": "text",
                        "item_content": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "content": "(iii). How many ways you can modify this scheme to make it stable when the CFL condition is satisfied. "
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                193,
                293,
                801,
                391
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "4. Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "C"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "D"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "in "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\mathbb { C } ^ { n \\times n }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "be Hermitian matrices. Denote their eigenvalues by "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                193,
                398,
                801,
                431
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\lambda_ {1} \\geq \\lambda_ {2} \\geq \\dots \\geq \\lambda_ {n} \\quad \\text {a n d} \\quad \\mu_ {1} \\geq \\mu_ {2} \\geq \\dots \\geq \\mu_ {n},",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/0f71b69648d8c1ed87c82d13d3233fd20e5910c98d88d4df83c863c4295bbda5.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                290,
                437,
                702,
                455
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "respectively. Then it is known that "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                193,
                460,
                502,
                476
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\sum_ {i = 1} ^ {n} \\left(\\lambda_ {i} - \\mu_ {i}\\right) ^ {2} \\leq \\| C - D \\| _ {F} ^ {2}.",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/0ed4126e94a66aa34e5ae107644cd8b043e3475395f7893c689a93a1cd16d49a.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                378,
                481,
                616,
                523
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "1) Let "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "A"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "B"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "be in "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\mathbb { C } ^ { n \\times n }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ". Denote their singular values by "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                231,
                527,
                754,
                545
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\sigma_ {1} \\geq \\sigma_ {2} \\geq \\dots \\geq \\sigma_ {n} \\quad \\text {a n d} \\quad \\tau_ {1} \\geq \\tau_ {2} \\geq \\dots \\geq \\tau_ {n},",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/cb46cedf9cdbb875f93353e7c915ac54e29e130ffa0e237d755f449ed2f27f07.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                295,
                551,
                697,
                568
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "respectively. Prove that the following inequality holds: "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                255,
                573,
                732,
                590
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\sum_ {i = 1} ^ {n} \\left(\\sigma_ {i} - \\tau_ {i}\\right) ^ {2} \\leq \\| A - B \\| _ {F} ^ {2}.",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/abafc1c8a2fe90d854660274d4bbc4c5d378303d3d5bd295b640a35ea91021e1.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                381,
                594,
                613,
                637
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "2) Given "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "A \\ \\in \\ \\mathbb { R } ^ { n \\times n }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "and its SVD is "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "A \\ = \\ U \\Sigma V ^ { T }"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", where "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "U ="
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "\\left( \\mathbf { u } _ { 1 } , \\mathbf { u } _ { 2 } , \\ldots , \\mathbf { u } _ { n } \\right)"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": ", "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
                        "content": "V = \\left( \\mathbf { v } _ { 1 } , \\mathbf { v } _ { 2 } , \\ldots , \\mathbf { v } _ { n } \\right)"
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "are orthogonal matrices, and "
                    }
                ]
            },
            "bbox": [
                231,
                642,
                801,
                690
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "equation_interline",
            "content": {
                "math_content": "\\Sigma = \\operatorname {d i a g} \\left(\\sigma_ {1}, \\sigma_ {2}, \\dots , \\sigma_ {n}\\right), \\quad \\sigma_ {1} \\geq \\sigma_ {2} \\geq \\dots \\geq \\sigma_ {n} \\geq 0.",
                "math_type": "latex",
                "image_source": {
                    "path": "images/3b48744c6c0baf576dfbc35e3ecd9f53975d4d823de439985c8cb811851174ba.jpg"
                }
            },
            "bbox": [
                275,
                697,
                717,
                715
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": {
                "paragraph_content": [
                    {
                        "type": "text",
                        "content": "Suppose "
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "equation_inline",
